Axxela Limited, a gas and power portfolio company, has received the ‘Most Sustainable Company’ award in the oil and gas sector in the African category from World Finance, a media outfit providing coverage and analysis of the financial industry, international business landscape and the global economy. According to a statement, the 2021 World Finance Oil & Gas Awards highlights companies and organisations that are best equipped to thrive in the new business landscape while meeting the highest international standards. The organisers were quoted as saying, “During this past year, Axxela, as a pioneer private sector-led natural gas company, has continued to show dynamism and responsiveness to the operating environment while also leveraging transformations to enhance business prospects and embrace the future.” The statement said the award acknowledged Axxela’s commitment to sustainable business practices despite the challenges of COVID-19 pandemic, and a strong outlook for success in the future. Receiving the award on behalf of Axxela, the Chief Executive Officer, Mr Bolaji Osunsanya, expressed appreciation for the award and reiterated the company’s renewed commitment to building a sustainable business in the African energy space. “This award is a recognition of Axxela’s innovative and progressive approach to solving Africa’s energy challenges by providing industries and organisations with sustainable, dependable, and affordable energy solutions,” he said.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com